{
  "text": "It is easy to find that the exact solution has the form [CITATION_1] and the initial magnetic field B = (B r , B \u03d5 , B z ) satisfies the divergence-free condition (2.9). We use the proposed spectral-DG method to simulate this problem, in which the partition in the \u03d5-direction is fixed as L = 4. In Table 4 .1, errors with different norms are presented at T = 0.1 and third order optimal accuracy is attained. [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . We take the initial conditions [CITATION_4] \u03c1 = 25 36\u03c0 , u = (\u2212 sin(2\u03c0z), sin(2\u03c0r), 0),",
  "citation_candidates": [
